Explanation of how I derived the parameters:

- The POST /v1/posts controller action uses App\Http\Requests\Admin\PostsRequest for validation and then only uses the request data keys: ['title', 'content', 'posted_at', 'author_id', 'thumbnail_id'] when creating the Post.
- I inspected PostsRequest::rules() to determine which fields are required and their expected types/constraints:
  - title: required -> string
  - content: required -> string
  - posted_at: required|date -> a date/time string (use format: date-time)
  - author_id: required|exists:users,id -> integer id (required)
  - thumbnail_id: nullable|exists:media,id -> integer id, optional
- prepareForValidation() parses posted_at with Carbon::parse(), so posted_at should be supplied as a date/time string acceptable by strtotime/Carbon (mapped to format: date-time in the OpenAPI schema).
- The controller's store() only accepts the five keys above; slug is prepared but not included in the store->only() list, so I did not include it as an input parameter.
- Following Swagger 2.0, the POST body is represented as a single "body" parameter whose schema describes the JSON object with properties and required fields.

